<%= open_graph_tags title: "Higher quality search results on Tampa Devs Talent", description: "It's now easier than ever to hire a developer on Tampa Devs Talent. A new approach to search results promises to bring higher quality profiles to the top. Read on for how it works and how developers can improve their search rank.", image: image_url("opengraph/recommended.png") %>

<div class="bg-white px-6 py-8 md:py-16 lg:px-8">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-blue-950">
    <p class="text-base font-semibold leading-7 text-red-600">Announcing</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-blue-900 sm:text-4xl">Higher quality search results on Tampa Devs Talent</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-xl leading-8">It's now easier than ever to hire a developer on Tampa Devs Talent. A new approach to search results promises to bring higher quality profiles to the top. Read on for how it works and how developers can improve their search rank.</p>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-2xl">
      <p class="mt-8">Previously, new developer profiles appeared first. With no way to effect their rank, a developer's profile would be continuously pushed farther and farther down results. A great candidate could be buried on page 5!</p>
      <p class="mt-6">Now, sorting by "recommended" surfaces higher quality profiles to the top based on:</p>

      <ul role="list" class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-blue-950">
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/check_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-red-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span><strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Responsiveness.</strong> How frequently a developer responds to conversations.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/check_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-red-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span><strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Frequency.</strong> How often a developer’s profile is updated.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/check_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-red-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span><strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Completeness.</strong> How much of a developer’s profile is filled out.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/check_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-red-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span><strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Contributors.</strong> Developers contributing to the <%= link_to "source code", "https://github.com/tampadevs/talent.tampa.dev", class: "font-semibold underline text-blue-800" %> of Tampa Devs Talent.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/check_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-red-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span>And more (see below for a complete breakdown).</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-8">You can try the new system today by selecting <%= link_to "Recommended from the Sort dropdown", developers_path(sort: :recommended), class: "font-semibold underline text-blue-800" %>.</p>
    </div>

    <%= image_tag "recommended.png", class: "aspect-video rounded-xl bg-blue-50 object-cover mt-8", alt: "Sort awesome developers by recommended on Tampa Devs Talent." %>

    <div class="mt-16 max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-blue-900">How can developers increase their rank?</h2>
      <p class="mt-8">Developers have direct control over each criteria that contributes to their rank and can increase their rank by:</p>

      <ul role="list" class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-blue-950">
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/plus_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-green-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span>Responding to 90% of conversations &rarr; <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">20 points</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/plus_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-green-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span>Contributing to the <%= link_to "Tampa Devs Talent source code", "https://github.com/tampadevs/talent.tampa.dev", class: "font-medium underline" %> &rarr; <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">20 points</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/plus_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-green-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span>Adding a scheduling link &rarr; <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">20 points</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/plus_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-green-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span>Updating your profile every month &rarr; <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">20 points</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/plus_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-green-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span>Having a bio with more than 500 characters &rarr; <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">10 points</strong></span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-8">New developers to the platform will also receive a healthy <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">30 point boost</strong> for 7 days.</p>
      <p class="mt-6">Note that there is also behavior that can indicate a developer is no longer job searching or hasn’t put much effort into their profile. Here are ways a developer’s rank could decrease.</p>

      <ul role="list" class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-blue-950">
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/minus_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-red-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span>Responding to fewer than 50% of conversations &rarr; <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">20 point deduction</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/minus_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-red-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span>Having a bio with less than 50 characters &rarr; <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">20 point deduction</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <%= inline_svg_tag "icons/solid/minus_circle.svg", class: "mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-red-600", aria_hidden: true %>
          <span>Not updating your profile in 6+ months &rarr; <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-900">10 points</strong></span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-blue-900">Feedback</h2>
      <p class="mt-8">Note that this new system is still in beta! And we’d love to hear your feedback. Please <%= link_to "send us an email", "mailto:#{Rails.application.config.emails.support!}", class: "font-semibold underline text-blue-800" %> if you have ideas on how it could be improved or something looks weird.</p>
      <p class="mt-6">For transparency, the code powering the system is <%= link_to "available on GitHub", "https://github.com/tampadevs/talent.tampa.dev/blob/main/app/models/concerns/developers/search_score.rb", class: "font-semibold underline text-blue-800" %>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
